# Development Guide

## Setup and Installation
1. Install Hugo extended version
2. Run `npm install` to install dependencies
3. Use `hugo server` for local development

## Project Configuration
- Main configuration is in [hugo.yaml](mdc:hugo.yaml)
- Node.js configuration in [package.json](mdc:package.json)
- VS Code settings in `.vscode/`

## Development Practices
- Follow Hugo's templating conventions
- Use partials for reusable components
- Maintain clean separation of concerns
- Test changes locally before committing

## Build and Deployment
- GitHub Actions handle automated deployment
- Build artifacts are stored in `resources/`
- Production builds use environment-specific settings

## Code Quality
- Follow consistent code formatting
- Document complex template logic
- Use semantic naming conventions
- Keep templates DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)
